import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=50, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['x'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x-coordinates in the terrain?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['y'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['y'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['y'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of y-coordinates in the terrain?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['lumosity'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['lumosity'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['lumosity'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of lumosity values in the terrain?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['saturation'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['saturation'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median = {:.2f}'.format(data['saturation'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of saturation values in the terrain?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    terrain_types = data['name'].value_counts()
    plt.bar(terrain_types.index, terrain_types.values)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of terrain types in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
